TO PREVENT BAD PEOPLE FROM GETTING ABOUT THE CATTLE.

Take wormwood, gith, five-finger weed, and assafœtida; three cents'
worth of each; the straw of horse

<span id="page_41">p. 41</span>

beans, some dirt swept together behind the door of the stable and a
little salt. Tie these all up together with a tape, and put the bundle
in a hole about the threshold over which your cattle pass in and out,
and cover it well with lignum-vitæ wood. This will certainly be of use.

